---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Writings | Chaos With Clarity"
  description="Essays and poems by Abby — on ego, experience, technology, love, and being fully alive."
>

  <!-- ══ PAGE HEADER ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-inner">
      <p class="overline" style="color:var(--olive-accent);">All Writings</p>
      <h1 class="page-h1">Essays<br/>&amp; Poems</h1>
      <div class="header-rule"></div>
      <p class="page-sub">
        Ideas that stay with you the next time you're scrolling at 2am,<br class="br-d"/>
        or wondering why you still feel restless even when everything looks fine on paper.
      </p>
    </div>
    <!-- decorative large word -->
    <p class="header-bg-word" aria-hidden="true">words</p>
  </section>

  <div class="writings-wrap">

    <!-- ══ FREEDOM & OBSERVER ══════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="writings-section">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="section-num" aria-hidden="true">01</p>
        <div class="section-label-row">
          <span class="section-dot" style="background:var(--olive-bright);"></span>
          <h2 class="section-label-text" style="color:var(--olive-bright);">Freedom &amp; Observer</h2>
          <div class="section-line"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="poem-grid-3">
        <article class="poem-card anim-card" style="--card-accent:var(--olive-bright);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="Unstruck Silence (Anhat Nad)"
                 data-date="March 2026"
                 data-poem="It starts but never ends,
It is just life, nothing to amend.

Silence is louder than noise,
Once you hear it, it abides.

Anhat Nad, it is said,
The uncreated sound that spreads.
Not from anywhere near or far,
Always present, revealing scars.

Contradiction is life's way of being,
Fighting it is simply fleeing.

Give your heart a pause,
Breathe in and listen to the cosmos.
It enters you and penetrates deep,
Making every restless cell sleep.

I know it sounds absurd,
That is why words feel blurred.

It starts but never ends,
It is just life, nothing to amend.

Empty the weight you carry in your heart,
Just be, and let silence be the start.

A start not of something new,
But something in you you always knew.

You are so small, yet vast the roles you play,
Trying to be more as life slips away.

To be ahead is just a muse,
Your breaths are counted, if you choose to view.

See what you truly hold,
Let go of wanting, and be bold.

Let silence become your home,
Be less, not more.

Be less, not more."
                 data-reflection="">
          <p class="card-date">March 2026</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">Unstruck Silence<br/><em class="card-subtitle">(Anhat Nad)</em></h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--olive-bright);">
            <p>It starts but never ends,</p>
            <p>It is just life, nothing to amend.</p>
            <p>Silence is louder than noise,</p>
            <p>Once you hear it, it abides.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--olive-bright);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>

        <article class="poem-card anim-card" style="--card-accent:var(--olive-bright);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="Let the Body Sync"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="I take a few breaths,
My heart ponders and wants rest,
Not from the chase or grind,
But to be still and just be kind,
Kind to my own self,
To feel the sync and how body and mind connect,
The integration begins within,
The universe then aligns and spins,
Spewing out all I want,
Stripping away the inessential thoughts,
Just be and the moment in time,
No rush to be ahead in line,
Walk with my own pace,
Knowing I always have grace,
I move the earth and stars,
When I am me and the cosmos just a macrocosm of my own heart."
                 data-reflection="This poem came from a morning when I was exhausted — not from doing too much, but from trying too hard to become something. The body knows things the mind refuses to accept. When I finally stopped striving and just breathed, everything settled.">
          <p class="card-date">2025</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">Let the Body Sync</h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--olive-bright);">
            <p>I take a few breaths,</p>
            <p>My heart ponders and wants rest,</p>
            <p>Not from the chase or grind,</p>
            <p>But to be still and just be kind.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--olive-bright);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>

        <article class="poem-card anim-card" style="--card-accent:var(--olive-bright);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="Let Me Be Conscious"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="Let me breathe today, let me be conscious,
Let me be free today, let me be outrageous,
Let me feel the pain I keep hiding,
Let me kiss a plant today I keep avoiding,
Let me be me without any validations,
Let me express myself without any questions,
If I could live like this for a moment,
I have lived it all, there remains no obligation,
If I die, I don't wanna be remembered,
If I live today, I wanna be felt with your full conscious,
If I could bring a small change, I have done my part,
If I make someone smile today, I have been kind to my own heart,
In all those dreams and aspirations, there was a selfishness I couldn't see,
My well wishers instead telling me let it be,
Run after all the things you will regret,
Keep skipping life like everyone and die with a heart that's sad,
Hope for a new life, begin it all anew,
Forget the past and run to the future shining like hue,
My heart said, it will be the same in the future as it was in the past,
If you can't feel the fresh air today and the dew on the morning grass,
Each breath felt is what you actually lived,
Being present to every second this life brings,
Being afraid you will lose what you have,
If you can appreciate each second without dread,
I am what I am, I will always be,
I don't want to imagine what I could be,
Let me accept the now and myself as it is,
Maybe I realize how perfect it all is,
Nothing could have been better, it's my journey,
A journey not to become,
A journey to just be and shed what the world unto me has done,
Let me breathe today, let me be conscious,
Let me be free today, let me be outrageous!"
                 data-reflection="This is the poem I come back to when I start performing life instead of living it. There's a difference between having a life and feeling it. This is about choosing to feel it — even the uncomfortable parts, especially the uncomfortable parts.">
          <p class="card-date">2025</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">Let Me Be Conscious</h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--olive-bright);">
            <p>Let me breathe today, let me be conscious,</p>
            <p>Let me be free today, let me be outrageous,</p>
            <p>Let me feel the pain I keep hiding.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--olive-bright);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ══ INNER WORK ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="writings-section">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="section-num" aria-hidden="true">02</p>
        <div class="section-label-row">
          <span class="section-dot" style="background:var(--olive-accent);"></span>
          <h2 class="section-label-text" style="color:var(--olive-accent);">Inner Work</h2>
          <div class="section-line"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="poem-grid-3">
        <article class="poem-card anim-card" style="--card-accent:var(--olive-accent);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="The Mirror"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="See yourself in the mirror and identify,
Are those really you and your beautiful eyes?
Beautiful they seem from outside,
But it's your perspective, not the sight.
You have changed and grown a lot,
The body tells you, but maybe your heart not.
I see the kindness of time,
It evolves us without a whine.
When I look in the mirror, I want to see
The way I see myself and not from the world I flee.
I will be me, just give me time.
Oh fool, you never know what's your crime.
This moment is all you have,
You are changing every passing breath.
Realise the beauty of it now,
Otherwise just look in the mirror and bow.
Respect yourself but don't be proud,
Throw away all your doubts.
What is in you, you see outside,
Mirror just a reflection and not a sight!"
                 data-reflection="">
          <p class="card-date">2025</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">The Mirror</h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--olive-accent);">
            <p>See yourself in the mirror and identify,</p>
            <p>Are those really you and your beautiful eyes?</p>
            <p>What is in you, you see outside.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--olive-accent);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>

        <article class="poem-card anim-card" style="--card-accent:var(--olive-accent);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="Beyond Words"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="I see language is just words,
Assigned meaning to not be absurd.
Sharing ideas and experiences, it's all,
But as we humans evolve,
Lies and deceit those words conceal.
Thinking overrides what we feel.
The energy, the heart, not real things,
But our motives and desires, it seems.
Dividing and spreading a deep scar,
I am this and they are different from what we are.
Beneath it all, the hearts beat the same,
Feel the energy, not what words claim.
You will find the same ignite,
Same humans, just different sight.
Expand yourself beyond the words,
Let us be one beyond these mere words.

Oh! So I wish I could speak it aloud,
But then again they are words, no doubt.
Just stillness and a kind smile,
A deep caress for humans and all life.
It could work wonders and be heard,
More genuine, not absurd.
But for this, it has to start,
Let it be from my own heart."
                 data-reflection="">
          <p class="card-date">2025</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">Beyond Words</h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--olive-accent);">
            <p>I see language is just words,</p>
            <p>Thinking overrides what we feel.</p>
            <p>Expand yourself beyond the words.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--olive-accent);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>

        <article class="poem-card anim-card" style="--card-accent:var(--olive-accent);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="The Right Eyes"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="Have seen a lot of eyes,
But nothing so mesmerising where depth abides.
Reflection of pain and suffering in life,
But kindness and the sparks it ignites.
Then a thought passes by,
Life is beautiful, just need the right eyes!"
                 data-reflection="">
          <p class="card-date">2025</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">The Right Eyes</h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--olive-accent);">
            <p>Have seen a lot of eyes,</p>
            <p>But nothing so mesmerising where depth abides.</p>
            <p>Life is beautiful, just need the right eyes!</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--olive-accent);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>

        <!-- ── CONSCIOUSNESS TRILOGY ── Part I, II, III ─────────── -->
        <article class="poem-card anim-card trilogy-card" style="--card-accent:var(--olive-accent);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="Forest of Consciousness"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="On a search, lost in the forest of consciousness,
Thoughts falling like rain,
Flooding the ground with pain,
Which path is mine, I know,
Green, or buried under snow?
I can't find the start,
Misery, I know my path,
Or so I believe, to give this heart relief.
The end is near but the start is far,
It's like the moon and the stars,
The sun doesn't burn me — my own thoughts inflame,
No one to blame, yet I feel the world's the same,
Trying to catch the rainbow,
Though it doesn't exist, I know,
Illusions all around, silence louder than sound,
Just one ray of light, one peak in sight,
From where I can leap, out of this sleep,
Lost to be found, rooted in my own ground,
Planted the trees myself, in this forest of consciousness."
                 data-reflection="Part I of the Consciousness Trilogy. The poet is lost inside the mind's own forest — and realises, at the end, that she planted the trees herself. Continue with Part II: I Am That, then Part III: The Journey.">
          <p class="card-series">Consciousness Trilogy · Part I of III</p>
          <p class="card-date">2025</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">Forest of<br/>Consciousness</h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--olive-accent);">
            <p>On a search, lost in the forest of consciousness,</p>
            <p>Thoughts falling like rain,</p>
            <p>Flooding the ground with pain.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--olive-accent);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>

        <article class="poem-card anim-card trilogy-card" style="--card-accent:var(--olive-accent);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="I Am That"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="Day begins, just a hearty smile to the sun,
Rays of light and hope return,
Each passing moment, second to none,
Every second, I stay in the now as one,
All doubts vanish, even the how,
No misery and pain to bow,
Thoughts still there like the clouds,
Waiting for rain, relief it shouts,
Why do I run this maze,
Lost in my mind, or just a craze,
Turning slowly, days go by,
Doubts, misery all by the side to creep and cry,
Then again I return to the now,
Smiling at a dream the mind created somehow,
Though I was wide awake,
Felt like nightmares waiting to break,
Breaking from inside, just like a cocoon,
Waiting like a butterfly, to bloom soon,
Lost in the stillness of the rays,
They bestowed something the heart craves,
If I could expand myself out,
I am the consciousness, I am that,
Just need to realize, and know that,
Which created all this, abstract and vast,
As the moon slowly burns,
Inside the home I return!!"
                 data-reflection="Part II of the Consciousness Trilogy. The poet moves through the mind's noise and returns — arriving at the realisation: I am the consciousness, I am that. Begin with Part I: Forest of Consciousness. End with Part III: The Journey.">
          <p class="card-series">Consciousness Trilogy · Part II of III</p>
          <p class="card-date">2025</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">I Am That</h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--olive-accent);">
            <p>Every second, I stay in the now as one,</p>
            <p>I am the consciousness, I am that,</p>
            <p>Inside the home I return.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--olive-accent);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>

        <article class="poem-card anim-card trilogy-card" style="--card-accent:var(--olive-accent);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="The Journey"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="The journey is long, but there's a start,
The journey to myself, to my own heart.

It begins in time, though timeless,
It's a journey of miles, without a step.

The more I travelled, the farther I got,
The more I thought, time didn't stop.

It had to begin, not somewhere far,
The day I stopped chasing, looked at my own scar.

The journey of eternity, the journey of lives,
The journey of a river, nowhere it resides.

From a small waterfall to the sea,
From sea to the clouds no one can see.

A journey of a moment, yet eternities went by,
The journey of joy, but filled with cries.

Not the journey that society preaches,
The journey to discover it's beyond your reaches.

The journey of sun and earth in the sky,
Looks like a chase with everything spinning by.

The journey home, deep within myself,
The journey of oneness, from heaven to hell.

The journey of a million thoughts
That occupy my mind,
The journey of stillness
With no thoughts to bind.

The journey of love, the journey of bliss,
Pause, breathe, in the moment so you don't miss."
                 data-reflection="Part III of the Consciousness Trilogy — the integration. After getting lost in the forest and realising I am that, this poem asks: what is the journey itself? Not outward, not even inward — but the movement of a river that arrives nowhere and everywhere. Begin with Part I: Forest of Consciousness.">
          <p class="card-series">Consciousness Trilogy · Part III of III</p>
          <p class="card-date">2025</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">The Journey</h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--olive-accent);">
            <p>The journey to myself, to my own heart.</p>
            <p>The day I stopped chasing, looked at my own scar.</p>
            <p>Pause, breathe, in the moment so you don't miss.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--olive-accent);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ══ ESSAYS ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="writings-section">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="section-num" aria-hidden="true">03</p>
        <div class="section-label-row">
          <span class="section-dot" style="background:var(--text-faint);"></span>
          <h2 class="section-label-text" style="color:var(--text-faint);">Essays</h2>
          <div class="section-line"></div>
          <span class="coming-badge">Coming soon</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="essay-grid">
        <div class="essay-card anim-card">
          <p class="essay-tag">Essay</p>
          <h3 class="essay-title">Who Owns You?</h3>
          <p class="essay-desc">How our gadgets, purchases, and rewards slowly start controlling our thoughts, time, and emotions, and how to take your attention back.</p>
          <span class="essay-soon">Coming soon</span>
        </div>
        <div class="essay-card anim-card">
          <p class="essay-tag">Essay</p>
          <h3 class="essay-title">We Were Never Meant for Intelligence</h3>
          <p class="essay-desc">Why AI is not the real threat. The real danger is humans forgetting that our edge was experience, not efficiency.</p>
          <span class="essay-soon">Coming soon</span>
        </div>
        <div class="essay-card anim-card">
          <p class="essay-tag">Essay</p>
          <h3 class="essay-title">Choosing Reality Over Symbols</h3>
          <p class="essay-desc">How we mistake words, labels, and spoilers for the real thing, and what it means to actually live your own experience.</p>
          <span class="essay-soon">Coming soon</span>
        </div>
        <div class="essay-card anim-card">
          <p class="essay-tag">Essay</p>
          <h3 class="essay-title">When Reading Rewires You</h3>
          <p class="essay-desc">How books quietly change the way you see situations, people, and yourself long after you close the last page.</p>
          <span class="essay-soon">Coming soon</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ══ PAIN & GRIEF ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="writings-section">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="section-num" aria-hidden="true">04</p>
        <div class="section-label-row">
          <span class="section-dot" style="background:var(--text-muted);"></span>
          <h2 class="section-label-text" style="color:var(--text-muted);">Pain &amp; Grief</h2>
          <div class="section-line"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="poem-grid-2">
        <article class="poem-card anim-card" style="--card-accent:var(--text-muted);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="The Walking Contradiction"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="I am not nice, but I am kind,
I see and observe, even when I am blind.
Blind to the way people act, but not the intent,
A softness in the heart, but the capacity to mend.

I am an introvert inside, but an extrovert by nature,
I am pure in my heart, but not in stature.
I am everything, yet nowhere,
I am everywhere, but nothing in despair.

I am a walking contradiction,
A fleeting shadow, a vivid depiction.
I am chaos wrapped in serenity,
A fragile soul, yet infinity.

I am the silence after the storm,
The shapeless mold, yet every form.
I am a paradox that you can't define,
A story unfinished, a journey divine.

I am something, a puzzle undone,
A spark in the dark, a rising sun."
                 data-reflection="I wrote this when I was trying to explain myself to someone and realized — I can't. And that's okay. The contradiction is not a flaw. It's the whole point.">
          <p class="card-date">2025</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">The Walking Contradiction</h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--text-muted);">
            <p>I am not nice, but I am kind,</p>
            <p>I see and observe, even when I am blind.</p>
            <p>I am chaos wrapped in serenity.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--text-muted);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>

        <article class="poem-card anim-card" style="--card-accent:var(--text-muted);"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="Nothing to Gain"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="People desire love, I want hate,
People want happiness, I want sadness to be my mate,
All the pain is temporary, suffering is my choice,
The reason I am here will not suffice,
It's a journey not a game of destination,
It's about the experiences you had without any expectations,
As slowly slowly, everything is lost,
I become nothing without any thought,
I reach my true state and found peace in all the pain,
Now I am everything where there is nothing to gain,
I have reached where it all started,
I am the oneness which in its eternity is all delighted!"
                 data-reflection="This poem looks dark from the outside. But it's actually the most peaceful thing I've ever written. When you stop trying to get something out of life — not in defeat, but in acceptance — you become everything. That's the paradox of surrender.">
          <p class="card-date">2025</p>
          <h3 class="card-title">Nothing to Gain</h3>
          <div class="card-preview" style="--prev-color:var(--text-muted);">
            <p>People desire love, I want hate,</p>
            <p>All the pain is temporary, suffering is my choice.</p>
            <p>Now I am everything where there is nothing to gain.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="card-cta" style="--cta:var(--text-muted);">Read full poem <i class="ph ph-arrow-right cta-arrow"></i></span>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ══ JOIN CTA ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="writings-cta anim-card">
      <p class="writings-cta-quote">
        These pieces arrive in your inbox.<br/>
        <em>Occasional. Honest. Worth it.</em>
      </p>
      <a href="/join" class="cta-btn">Get the Letters &rarr;</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ══ PAGE HEADER ══════════════════════════════════════════════ */
  .page-header {
    padding: 10rem 3rem 6rem;
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .page-header-inner {
    max-width: 72rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  .overline {
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.32em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .page-h1 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 9vw, 8rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--text);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 0.9;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .header-rule {
    width: 3rem;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--olive-accent);
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }
  .page-sub {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.95;
    font-weight: 300;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }
  /* large decorative word behind header */
  .header-bg-word {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -1.5rem;
    right: -1rem;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: clamp(6rem, 18vw, 16rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--border);
